  <div class="main-wrapper">

    <div class="tabs-wrapper">
      <div class="tabs-btn">
        <button class="w3-bar-item w3-button" onclick="openCheckTab('story')">STORY</button>
        <button class="w3-bar-item w3-button" onclick="openCheckTab('faq')">FAQ</button>
        <button class="w3-bar-item w3-button" onclick="openCheckTab('shipping')">SHIPPING</button>
        <button class="w3-bar-item w3-button" onclick="openCheckTab('warranty')">WARRANTY</button>
      </div>

      <div id="story" class="check-tab">
        <h2>Production</h2>
        <p>We have begin turning the prototype into the final product. We are in control of all steps of the process.<br>It was conceptualized & designed by us in Brussels-Belgium. We itterate and build the prototypes in a garage in Brussels, and it will be assembled in Belgium as Well. Let's make things happen! Cheers.<br><br> The YodaCity Founders.</p>
        <div class="img-container">
          <%= image_tag('Checkout/Progress-bar@2x.png', class: "bar-progress") %>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div id="faq" class="check-tab" style="display:none">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <h3>The Yoda riding experience</h3>
        <div class="faq-question">
          <h5>Is this an e-bike, a moped, or what?</h5>
          <p>The Yoda bike was designed to provide the riding experience of a bike (everyone knows how to ride a bicycle), with the advantages of a motorcycle (you can go up to 45 km/h without sweating).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-question">
          <h5>Do I need a license/license plate/insurance to drive a Yoda?</h5>
          <p>You may need a license, license plate, and insurance depending on the laws of the country in which you ride. For instance in Belgium, you will need:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Either a type B license (regular car license), or an A3 or AM motorcycle license (which can be obtained if you are 16 or above).</li>
            <li>To apply for a license plate for class B mopeds. These begin with the letters “SB”.</li>
            <li>A liability insurance policy (”Burgerlijke Aansprakelijkheid”/“Responsabilité Civile”).</li>
          </ul>
          <p>We will provide you with detailed step-by-step guidance when delivering your Yoda to you.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-question">
          <h5>Do I need a helmet?</h5>
          <p>Yes, most countries have laws requiring to wear helmets. For instance, in Belgium, you’ll need to wear a moped/motorcycle E-marked helmet.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-question">
          <h5>Can I drive a Yoda on bike lanes?</h5>
          <p>It depends on the laws of the country in which you ride. For instance in Belgium, you can in most cases use bike lanes marked by this sign</p>
          <div class="img-bike-lanes-container">
            <%= image_tag('Checkout/Bike-lanes-sign.png', class: "bike-lanes") %>
          </div>
          <p>More information is available<a href="https://www.permisdeconduire-online.be/theorie/theorie-permis-am/ou-devez-vous-rouler-avec-votre-motoclyclette"> here (français)</a> and <a href="https://www.gratisrijbewijsonline.be/theorie/leerstof-rijbewijs-am/fietser-fietspad-oversteekplaats"> here (néerlandais)</a>.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-question">
          <h5>Can I put a bike rack on a Yoda?</h5>
          <p>No. Our betas testers typically carry things around with a backpack. Unlike when riding a bike, you won’t sweat so it’s not uncomfortable.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-question">
          <h5>What if I don’t have a smartphone, or my phone runs out of battery?</h5>
          <p>We will provide you with a smartcard to allow you to unlock your Yoda without your phone.</p>
        </div>

        <h3>Pre-order</h3>
        <div class="faq-question">
          <h5>When will my Yoda be delivered to me?</h5>
          <p>We’re doing everything in our power for this date to be as soon as possible. We are targeting Spring 2020. Bear in mind however that some things are out of our hands. These include our suppliers timelines and the timeline of the administration providing the homologation. We will keep you informed of any significant delay.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-question">
          <h5>What is included in the price?</h5>
          <p>The price of a fully-functional street-legal Yoda is 2990 EUR and includes VAT. A charger costs 100 EUR VAT included. The price does not include delivery costs, should you wish to have us bring your Yoda to you instead of picking it up in Uccle, Belgium.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-question">
          <h5>Why should I pre-order?</h5>
          <p>A pre-order guarantees you that you’ll receive one of the Yodas we manufacture in the next batch, which will be limited to 200 Yodas. We do not guarantee the current price and availability of Yodas in the future.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-question">
          <h5>What if I change my mind and do not want a Yoda anymore?</h5>
          <p>Our terms and conditions of pre-order apply. As provided by consumer protection laws, you have up to 14 days after we deliver to you to change your mind and return us the Yoda to receive a full refund.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-question">
          <h5>Can I order one if I don’t live in Belgium?</h5>
          <p>At the moment, pre-orders can only be made for delivery in Belgium. Contact us to be updated about availability in your country.</p>
        </div>


      </div>

      <div id="shipping" class="check-tab" style="display:none">
        <h2>Shipping</h2>
        <p>Paris is the capital of France.</p>
      </div>

      <div id="warranty" class="check-tab" style="display:none">
        <h2>Warranty</h2>
        <p>Tokyo is the capital of Japan.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

